me":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Boson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of North German, Danish, and Norwegian   Boysen  .","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Boie</i> (Old English <i>Boia</i>) + <i>-son</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Boysen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerd, Hans, Erwin, Hermann, Juergen, Lorenz, Siegfried.","North German, Danish, and Norwegian: patronymic from the personal name   Boye  ."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter de Boson III was born about 1120, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Boson I, was 22 and his mother, wife John Boson or Bozonn I, was 17. He married de Boson in 1139, in Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1120–":"umbes 1120–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1122–Female":"1122–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","1139":"1139","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1104":"1104","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","about 1120":"umbes 1120","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolkshire, , , England":"Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1120–":"noin 1120–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1122–Female":"1122–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1104–Female":"1104–Kuollut","1139":"1139","about 1140":"noin 1140","1104":"1104","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","about 1120":"noin 1120","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norfolkshire, , , England":"Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"about 1120–":"environ 1120–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1122–Female":"1122–Décédée","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1104–Female":"1104–Décédée","1139":"1139","about 1140":"environ 1140","1104":"1104","1100":"1100","1122":"1122","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","about 1120":"environ 1120","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Norfolkshire, , , England":"Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Peter de Boson III est né environ 1120, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, John de Boson I, avait 22 ans et sa mère, wife John Boson or Bozonn I, avait 17 ans. Il a épousé de Boson en 1139, à Norfolk, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1120–":"um 1120–Verstorben","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben","1122–Female":"